            . I am a watchman. On the 1st of October, about twelve o'clock at night, I stopped the prisoner in Whitecross-street, with a bundle under her arm, and asked what was in it; she said it was a pair of blankets - I took her to the watch-house. Morran afterwards claimed them.</p>
