                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18241028-95-victim914 t18241028-95-viclabel510"></join>. The prisoner is a stranger. I missed these blankets off the counter a few minutes before twelve o'clock on the night of the 1st of October; I paid 2 l. 8 s. for them six or eight months ago, but have never used them.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was in Finsbury-square, and asked a man the way to Smithfield; he said, turn to the right, and said,</p>
               <p>"Here, lay hold of this bundle while I go over the way." I went on till the watchman took me - I said a man had given them to me.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 34.</p>
               <p>Of <rs id="t18241028-95-verdict511" type="verdictDescription">
